# 🚀 Terraform AWS Nginx Deployment

This project demonstrates how to provision AWS infrastructure using Terraform and deploy a web server using Nginx on an EC2 instance.

---

## 🧠 Project Overview

In this project, I built a complete AWS infrastructure using Terraform and successfully hosted a web server accessible via a public IP.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Terraform  
- AWS EC2  
- AWS VPC  
- Amazon Linux  
- Nginx  
- SSH  

---

## ⚙️ Infrastructure Components

- Custom VPC  
- Public Subnets  
- Internet Gateway  
- Route Tables  
- Security Groups (SSH & HTTP access)  
- EC2 Instance  

---

## 🚀 Deployment Steps

1. Created VPC and networking components using Terraform  
2. Configured public subnet and routing via Internet Gateway  
3. Launched EC2 instance with security group  
4. Connected using SSH  
5. Installed and started Nginx  
6. Accessed application via public IP  

